docs.lead_paragraph: GENEVA, Oct. 29. -- Acceptances of sanctions against the Italian Government poured in on Geneva today, the only disappointment being the Swiss refusal to accept fully the boycott of Italian goods stipulated in Proposal 3.
docs.abstract: Poland, Denmark, Uruguay, Netherlands, Bulgaria, Yugoslavia, Czechoslovakia, Turkey and Greece accept all 4 sanctions, making 29 full acceptances; Argentina and Spain agree to proposal 2; Norway, Denmark, Estonia and Bulgaria ask till Nov 15 for application of economic sanctions; League notes change in neutrality policy; com of 52 to meet Oct 31

headline.main: 29 NATIONS AGREE TO FULL SANCTIONS; Acceptances Pile Up in Geneva, but the Swiss Bar Complete Boycott of Italian Goods.

docs.lead_paragraph: Limited fluctuations were the rule in the foreign exchange market last week. The turnover also showed contraction due in part to the holiday in some of the European countries on Friday, and to the disposition of bankers to rest their commitments beyond the routine to possible developments in the war area.

docs.snippet: MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay, Nov. 5. -- The Argentine Government has established a tight censorship to prevent news from getting out regarding Sunday's elections in the provinces of Buenos Aires and Cordoba. The Buenos Aires newspapers received here describe...
docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay, Nov. 5. -- The Argentine Government has established a tight censorship to prevent news from getting out regarding Sunday's elections in the provinces of Buenos Aires and Cordoba. The Buenos Aires newspapers received here describe the elections as the most fraudulent, scandalous and violent in the country's history.
docs.abstract: Press charges frauds in Congressional elections in provinces of Buenos Aires and Cordoba; strict censorship

headline.main: FRAUD IS CHARGED IN ARGENTINE POLL; Provincial Elections Sunday Called Most Scandalous in History of Nation. 3 KILLED, SCORE WOUNDED Strict Censorship Is Invoked -Gangs Kept Opposition From Voting, Newspapers State.
